<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wijes., Yong Wang bis, Camporesi &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" genus="Italica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Italica heraclei" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="heraclei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">Italica heraclei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLUCC 20-0227) shows morphological characters that are typical for the genus, including coriaceous ascomata; filamentous, branched and septate pseudoparaphyses; and hyaline to yellowish-brown ascospores. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wijes., Yong Wang bis, Camporesi &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" genus="Italica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Italica heraclei" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="heraclei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">Italica heraclei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" genus="Italica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Italica" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">Italica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by its cylindrical asci and vertically aseptate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F6199310" captionText="Figure 3. Italica heraclei (MFLU 18 - 1906). a-b. Ascomata on a dead stem of Heracleum sphondylium (Apiales, Apiaceae). c. Section of an ascoma. d. Peridium. e. Pseudoparaphyses. f-j. Asci. k-n. Ascospores. o-p. Colonies on PDA from upper (o) and lower (p) sides. Scale bars: a-b = 200 µm, c = 100 µm, d-j = 20 µm, k-n = 10 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e59648.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479944" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">3</figureCitation>
) and uniseriate-arranged ascospores in asci.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">
From the comparison of the SSU, ITS, LSU and TEF sequences of 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. heraclei" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" rank="species" species="heraclei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">I. heraclei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLUCC 20-0227) and 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. luzulae" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" rank="species" species="luzulae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">I. luzulae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLUCC 14-0932, type species) strains, we detected 3/949 (0.31%), 67/517 (12.95%), 20/796 (2.51%) and 32/619 (5.16%) differences, respectively. From the comparison of SSU, ITS, LSU and TEF nucleotides of 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. heraclei" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" rank="species" species="heraclei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">I. heraclei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. achilleae" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" rank="species" species="achilleae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">I. achilleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLUCC 14-0955), we found 1/950 (0.1%), 64/517 (12.37%), 7/796 (1.13%) and 28/619 (4.52%) differences, respectively. According to the results of our integrative taxonomy approach, we described 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. heraclei" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" rank="species" species="heraclei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">I. heraclei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLUCC 20-0227) as a new species.
</paragraph>
